text:
Hi beautiful people!
<!channel>

Happy Saturday!!! :raised_hands: Life is beautiful isn’t it???
Here are some winners for the events coming up months:

1. October ---> Botanical gardens --> Date/Time: TBD 
2. November--> Jeju Sauna + KKBQ --> Approx Sun. Nov 19 (Let’s vote on which kbbq place you want based on prices and options they provide and location. I will default to one closest to Jeju Sauna in Duluth then we all drive back down together or one closer to Atlanta for those only joining for food) 
    a. Jeju Island (<https://jejusauna.com/|https://jejusauna.com/>)
    b. Iron age (<https://ironagekoreansteakhouse.com/|https://ironagekoreansteakhouse.com/>) :moyai:
    c. Top Korean (<https://www.topkoreanbbq.com/|https://www.topkoreanbbq.com/>) :poultry_leg:
    d. 92929 (<https://maps.app.goo.gl/qUCrsuwfUiFvLq5VA?g_st=ic|https://maps.app.goo.gl/qUCrsuwfUiFvLq5VA?g_st=ic>) :nine:
Thanks for the support from TAPIA and my talk! We are largest online MSCS so here are some OMSCS students that  I surprisingly met but also came to show support from other parts of the US (Arkansas, New Jersey, California, and more)!!

Ps for those who want to do a hackathon on campus w/ HackGT and <@U0495G3QQ1W> <@U041DBXGPC4> <@U040V1EQYMS> sign up today deadline this weekend (<https://registration.hexlabs.org/647fee51768e521dc8ef88e0|https://registration.hexlabs.org/647fee51768e521dc8ef88e0>)
If you want to do a hackathon but don't want to be on their team you don't have to. It's good to meet new people, learn and make something for your portfolio or have fun or mentor others too.

Hope you’re having a great weekend!

Much love from Texas,
Cherie Lum
